U.S. Stocks Erase Drop as Fifth Third Helps Lead Rally in Banking Shares

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-05-16T14:14:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/u-s-stocks-erase-drop-as-fifth-third-helps-lead-rally-in-banking-shares.html
U.S. stocks erased losses as Fifth
Third Bancorp paced a rally in banks after analysts advised
buying the shares, while Lowe’s Cos. helped lead consumer
companies lower after earnings trailed analyst estimates.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index fell less than 0.1 percent
to 1,337.02 at 10:08 a.m. in  New York  after slumping 0.5 percent
in early trading. The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  lost 24.82
points, or 0.2 percent, to 12,570.93 after dropping 0.5 percent.  Earlier losses came as international finance leaders de
bated extending aid to Greece and New York manufacturing growth
slowed more than forecast.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  